            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C) In nomine domini Dei et hominis. Anno incarnationis eiusdem millesimo
                        centesimo vigesimo quarto, mensis iulii die quinta, indictione secunda. Cum
                        rectores ęcclesiarum semper religionis instantiam augere atque in meliorem
                        statum quantum divinitus eis conceditur debeant reducere neglegentię reus
                        arguitur qui prelatus hoc facere non nititur. Quam rem nos <persName
                            key="#Bishops #Episcopal_diploma" ref="#people/3567"
                            >Sinebaldus</persName>
                        <placeName key="#Bishops #Dioecesis #Mother_churches" ref="#places/41"
                            >Paduanus</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> licet indignus mente perpendentes pro
                        amore Dei cuius opus esse credimus ac remissione peccatorum nostrorum et pro
                        amore domni <rs key="#Popes">pape</rs>
                        <persName>Calixti</persName> cuius nichilominus voluntatem cognovimus,
                            <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/2414"><rs
                                key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                            <placeName key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/4105"
                            >Prataliense</placeName></orgName> in nostro <rs
                            key="#Dioecesis #Mother_churches">episcopatu</rs> situm dilettissimo
                        patri nostro domno <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/3556"
                            >Herimanno</persName> venerabili <rs key="#Abbots">abbati</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Abbots" ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sancti Benedicti super
                            Padum</orgName> suisque successoribus catholicis communi consilio
                        fratrum ad religionis instituendę observantiam concedimus et presenti
                        scripto confirmamus, salvo iure nostro et successorum nostrorum episcoporum
                        catholicorum. Ita sane ut a nobis et a ceteris Paduanis qui pro tempore
                        fuerint episcopis oleum sanctum, consecrationes, ordinationes abbatis,
                        benedictiones et cętera episcopalia gratis et sine pravitate conferantur,
                        que nimirum abbas de religioso Sancti Benedicti monasterio semper
                        assummetur. Is etiam Paduano episcopo sicut proprio pastori debitam semper
                        obedientiam conferat ad capitula generalia et ad alias necessarias
                        ęcclesiasticas utilitates ad dandum consilium et auxilium sine exactione si
                        vocatus fuerit suam presentiam exhibeat nisi iustam habeat excusationem,
                        salvo in omnibus ordine suo. Et ne religiosa militia turbetur, sed sine
                        inquietudine Dei servitiis vacare valeat, hoc quoque presenti addimus
                        concessioni ut neque nobis neque ulli ex successoribus nostris aliquo in
                        tempore liceat quicquam de rebus temporalibus a prefati monasterii abbate
                        per violentiam auferre vel eo invito extorquere vel exigere, nisi sponte et
                        karitative aliquid impendere voluerit. Ut autem huius concessionis series a
                        nobis esse formata credatur et ut plenarie corroboretur, duas sub uno tenore
                            <rs key="#Episcopal_diploma">paginas</rs> per manum publici tabellionis
                        scribi ac proprii sigilli impressione muniri iussimus. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Episcopal_diploma #Priests"><name
                                ref="Grimaldus(/presbiter">Grimalduas</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs>
                        <rs key="#Witness">subscripsi</rs>. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Episcopal_diploma #Priests"><name
                                ref="Hubertus/presbiter/de Salvia">Ubertus</name></persName>
                        presbiter de Salvia subscripsi. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Episcopal_diploma #Priests"><name
                                ref="Hubertus/presbiter">Ybertus</name></persName> presbiter manu
                        mea subscripsi. Ego <persName key="#Witness #Episcopal_diploma #Priests"
                                ><name ref="Vivianus/presbiter">Vivianus</name></persName> presbiter
                        manu mea subscripsi. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Episcopal_diploma #Deacons"><name ref="Milo/diaconus"
                                >Milo</name></persName> diaconus subscripsi. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Episcopal_diploma #Deacons"><name ref="Nicolaus/diaconus"
                                >Nicolaus</name></persName> manu mea <rs key="#Deacons"
                            >diaconus</rs> subscripsi. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Episcopal_diploma #Subdeacons"><name
                                ref="Vualingus/subdiaconus">Walengus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Subdeacons">subdiaconus</rs> subscripsi. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Episcopal_diploma #Subdeacons"><name
                                ref="Torengus/subdiaconus">Torengus</name></persName> subdiaconus
                        manu mea subscripsi. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Episcopal_diploma #Subdeacons"><name
                                ref="Hubertus/subdiaconus">Ubertus</name></persName> subdiaconus
                        subscripsi. Ego <persName key="#Witness #Episcopal_diploma #Subdeacons"
                                ><name ref="Lemizo/subdiaconus">Lemizo</name></persName> subdiaconus
                        manu mea subscripsi. (M) <persName
                            key="#Episcopal_diploma #Causidicus #Tabellio"><name
                                ref="Ionas/causidicus et tabellio">Ionas</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Causidicus">causidicus</rs> necnonque <rs key="#Tabellio"
                            >tabellio</rs> dictus lumine quę vidi bis scripsi menteque fixi. </ab>
